      "span_text": "Based on the eGFR, the degree of graft function was classified as chronic kidney disease (CKD) stage I (i.e., normal kidney function and eGFR ≥ 90 mL/min/1.73 m 2 ), stage II (i.e., mild loss of kidney function and eGFR 60-89 mL/min/1.73 m 2 ), stage IIIa (i.e., mild to moderate loss of kidney function and eGFR 45-59 mL/min/1.73 m 2 ), stage IIIb (i.e., moderate to severe loss of kidney function and eGFR 30-44 mL/min/1.73 m 2 ), stage IV (i.e., severe loss of kidney function and eGFR 15-29 mL/min/1.73 m 2 ), or stage V (i.e., kidney failure and eGFR < 15 mL/min/1.73 m 2 ) [CITATION_2] ."
